cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on vehicular communication and the IEEE 802.11p standard, which are related to networking and wireless communication. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses congestion control algorithms and their impact on communication performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a modification to the Reactive DCC algorithm to improve its performance. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the Cooperative Awareness Message (CAM) controllers, which are related to security and privacy in vehicular communication. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also less likely but possible as the Reactive DCC algorithm is a distributed congestion control mechanism.
